Shape: Shape refers to the rows and columns in your dataset.  Shown as (rows x columns)
Type: The datatype of the column values.
Role: How the column should be used by machine learning algorithms.
Imputation: Imputation method to use in case of missing values.
Datasets: A dataset is a unique set of observations, variables, and values from which a model is built.
Models: A model is the type of algorithm selected for a dataset that is used for predictions.
Sessions: A session is a request that initiates the process of creating a model from a dataset.
Target: The target column is the one for which you want to predict the outcome.
